b'We\xe2\x80\x99re committed to improving the lives of all children and all families, especially during these unprecedented times. The events of this past year have challenged us to adapt and rise to the occasion to meet the needs of our consumers, employees, supply chains, and communities around the world. 
 
We shifted our attention to support our employees and communities throughout the COVID-19 pandemic, restated our commitment to diversity & inclusion and continued to make progress against our long-term goals. We pledged to eliminate plastic in our packaging by the end of 2022, expanded the Hasbro Toy Recycling program to six countries and continued to conduct full human rights and ethical sourcing reviews of our suppliers. We even became the first toy and game company to pilot the Higg Index to further measure the environmental impacts of our supply chain.
 
Read more about our progress and goals for the future in our newly issued 2019-2020 Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) Update.'

b"#Repost @livingnotes: #AD: A little imagination and some family fun never hurt anybody, right?! Teaming up with @Hasbro to throw a couple of ideas your way.
.
Change your game nights to a game DAYS. Same thing during a different hour will occupy your noisy crew. Game of Life is FUN. What do you play?
.
Get competitive. Make two kids compete against each other or complete with your little boss, but seeing who wins is just...exciting. Evyianne and Elia\xe2\x80\x99s fav Play-Doh sets (like this cute Cluck-a-Dee Chicken!) work like magic. We all can use a little de-stressing here.
.
Imagination time. Kids may not be able to interact with their friends because of social distancing, but there is no shortage of imagination. Let kids run WILD with it. Throw out a couple of story ideas for them.  Kids will play for hours when given an idea and left alone. Here is a pro tip: want to know what\xe2\x80\x99s going on in your kids minds? Listen in carefully to what they are saying to their toy friends. They tell ALL.
.
You know, this time is tough. BUT! Kids' smiles make the world a little brighter. There are still amazing memories being made. Even during quarantine!
.
What are you doing to keep your little ones happy?
.
(All toys are sold separately)  #PlayDoh #BringHomeTheFun #DisneyPrincess
